<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-108-152 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 965 220</DOCID><JOURNAL>CSN  July 8 1991 n521 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM, Apple ally on RISC PC: Apple to offer systems using RS/6000chip; software venture formed.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sperling, Ed.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple and IBM agree to form a joint venture to develop, market andlicense an object oriented-based open systems platform.andP;  The jointventure will also develop a software that integrates AppleMacintosh computers into IBM environments.andP;  As part of the pactApple will develop a workstation that features a scaled-downsingle chip version of IBM's RS/6000 microprocessor to its line ofdesktops in 1992.andP;  The pact with Apple and previous agreementswith Lotus Development Corp and Novell Inc places IBM in astrategic position in its fight against Microsoft's domination ofthe desktop software industry.andP;  Industry analysts say theagreement also provides users with such key qualities such asclient/ server architecture and universal networks.andP;  The pact,according to analysts, also undermines Sun Microsystems Inc'sAdvanced Computing Environment which is developing a RISC-basedworkstation that will use Microsoft's New Technology kernel to runseveral operating systems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Contracts)International Business Machines Corp. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    AAPL; IBM.andO;Topic:     Open SystemsCooperative AgreementStrategic PlanningIndustry AnalysisContractsProduct DevelopmentMicroprocessors.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablephotograph.andO;Caption:   Alliance goals. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>